# рџ§  1. Mutating Methods (change original array)

---

## рџ”№ 1. `push()`

рџ‘‰ Adds element(s) to the **end**

```js
let arr = [1,2];
arr.push(3,4);

console.log(arr); // [1,2,3,4]
```

вњ” Returns: new length
вњ” Use: adding items

---

## рџ”№ 2. `pop()`

рџ‘‰ Removes last element

```js
let arr = [1,2,3];
arr.pop();

console.log(arr); // [1,2]
```

вњ” Returns: removed element

---

## рџ”№ 3. `unshift()`

рџ‘‰ Adds element(s) at **start**

```js
let arr = [2,3];
arr.unshift(1);

console.log(arr); // [1,2,3]
```

---

## рџ”№ 4. `shift()`

рџ‘‰ Removes first element

```js
let arr = [1,2,3];
arr.shift();

console.log(arr); // [2,3]
```

---

## рџ”№ 5. `splice()` в­ђ (VERY IMPORTANT)

рџ‘‰ Add/remove/replace elements

```js
